{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_140","type":"agent_message","text":"Research execution is complete.\n\nPrimary deliverable: [REPORT.md](/workspaces/narrative-space-llm-65e5-codex/REPORT.md)  \nQuick overview: [README.md](/workspaces/narrative-space-llm-65e5-codex/README.md)  \nCode guide: [CODE_WALKTHROUGH.md](/workspaces/narrative-space-llm-65e5-codex/CODE_WALKTHROUGH.md)\n\nKey result: a qualified yes. GPT-5.4-mini spatial narratives were strongly separable from human spatial texts. All non-length features classified human vs LLM at 96.5% accuracy; spatial-only features reached 87.7% aggregate accuracy and 83.8% on the WritingPrompts prose-control subset. The main caveat is that R2R is genre-confounded because human texts are short route instructions while LLM outputs are stories.\n\nI used real OpenAI API generations: 114 GPT-5.4-mini calls, 49,394 total tokens, about USD 0.15 estimated from official OpenAI pricing. Sources used for pricing/model details: OpenAI model docs https://developers.openai.com/api/docs/models/gpt-5.4-mini and pricing page https://openai.com/api/pricing.\n\nValidation passed: scripts compile, cached generation has 114/114 outputs, corpus is balanced at 114 human and 114 LLM texts, figures are generated, and metrics match the report."}}
